"Hoshi Y., Mikami Y., Nagamine T., Watanabe K., Yamaguchi A., Yusa Y.","Freonless gas mixtures for glass RPC operated in streamer mode",2003,"Nuclear Instruments and Methods in Physics Research, Section A: Accelerators, Spectrometers, Detectors and Associated Equipment","508","1-2",,"56","62",,,10.1016/S0168-9002(03)01277-4,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0043166341&partnerID=40&md5=73e084b1cd47859b441e13d7622a8d73","Department of Physics, Tohoku University, Sendai 980-8578, Japan; Tohoku-Gakuin University, Tagajo 985-8537, Japan","Hoshi, Y., Department of Physics, Tohoku University, Sendai 980-8578, Japan; Mikami, Y., Tohoku-Gakuin University, Tagajo 985-8537, Japan; Nagamine, T., Tohoku-Gakuin University, Tagajo 985-8537, Japan; Watanabe, K., Tohoku-Gakuin University, Tagajo 985-8537, Japan; Yamaguchi, A., Tohoku-Gakuin University, Tagajo 985-8537, Japan; Yusa, Y., Tohoku-Gakuin University, Tagajo 985-8537, Japan","We have operated successfully glass Resistive Plate Counters (RPC) at the BELLE experiment by using a nonflammable gas mixture of 30% argon, 8% butane-silver and 62% freon, HFC-134a. This freon is nonozone depleting freon, but a freon has a high global warming potential in general. Thus a gas mixture for RPC might be desired to be freonless in the near future. We have tested the performance of glass RPC operated in streamer mode with a nonfreon gas mixture of argon, butane, CO2 and/or O2 gases, and found an efficiency of about 90%. © 2003 Elsevier Science B.V. All rights reserved.","Nonfreon; RPC; Streamer mode","Electric conductivity of gases; Freons; Mixtures; Particle detectors; Radiation counters; Gas mixtures; Gas detectors",,,,,,"Santonico, R., Cardarelli, R., (1981) Nucl. Instr. and Meth. A, 187, p. 377; Abe, K., Proceedings of the RPC97 (1998) Sci. Acta, 13 (2), p. 281. , Naples, Italy 1997; Abashian, A., (2000) Nucl. Instr. and Meth. A, 449, p. 112; (2000) KEK Progress Report, 2000 (4). , November; Abe, K., (1999) IEEE Trans. Nucl. Sci., NS-46-6, p. 2017; Abe, K., (2000) IEEE Trans. Nucl. Sci., NS-47-6, p. 1784; Yamaga, M., (2000) Nucl. Instr. and Meth. A, 456, p. 109; Lind, D.R., (1991) CRC Handbook of Radiation Chemistry, , Boca Raton, FL: CRC Press; Abe, K., (2000) Nucl. Instr. and Meth. A, 455, p. 397; Narita, S., (2001) IEEE Trans. Nucl. Sci., NS-48-3, p. 893; Ganter, S., (1998) Nucl. Instr. and Meth. A, 414, p. 182; Lewis, B., Elbe, G., (1938) Combustion, Flames and Explosions of Gases, , Cambridge: Cambridge University Press","Yamaguchi, A.; Tohoku-Gakuin University, Tagajo 985-8537, Japan; email: yamag@awa.tohoku.ac.jp","Fonte P.Fraga M.Ratti S.P.Santonico R.",,,"Proceedings of the Sixth International Workshop on Resistive P (RPC 2001)","26 November 2001 through 27 November 2001","Coimbra",61290,01689002,,NIMAE,,"English","Nucl Instrum Methods Phys Res Sect A",Conference Paper,Scopus,2-s2.0-0043166341
